“Babushka Dogs” have been all over Instagram and other social media and you can understand why. As the images below will soon make it clear — these dogs are as cute as any you’ve seen.

The world “babushka” means “grandmother or elderly woman” in Russian, BuzzFeed reminds us, but here in North America it is usually used to mean a “headscarf tied under the chin”. And that is the meaning that is applied here.
